Senate Resolution 366
By: Senators Robertson of the 29th and Albers of the 56th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing March 10, 2025, as Law Enforcement Appreciation Day at the Capitol and
2 commending law enforcement officers in Georgia; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Law Enforcement Appreciation Day at the Capitol exists to honor this state's
4 law enforcement officers for putting their lives on the line every day and to commend them
5 for everything they do; and
6 WHEREAS, Georgia law enforcement officers are highly trained professionals who work
7 overtime to ensure the safety of our communities and whose duties primarily involve the
8 enforcement of laws, protecting life & property, keeping the peace, and other public safety
9 related duties; and
10 WHEREAS, the Office of the Sheriff is the oldest law enforcement office known throughout
11 history; sheriffs are duly elected constitutional officers and the only lawfully commissioned
12 chief law enforcement officers in the country; and
13 WHEREAS, Georgia Police Departments provide police services in the State of Georgia that
14 are aimed at achieving more effective and efficient crime control, a reduced fear of crime,
15 an improved quality of life, and an improved police legitimacy through a proactive reliance
16 on community resources that seeks to minimize crime-causing conditions and ensures that
