17 all Georgia citizens are served in a professional, ethical, and equitable manner by
18 establishing strong commitments with all segments of society based on trust and positive,
19 professional relationships; and
20 WHEREAS, law enforcement officers from Georgia's state agencies, including the Georgia
21 State Patrol, Capitol Police, DNR, GBI, and other law enforcement agencies, work
22 cooperatively to enhance public safety by enforcing traffic laws and traffic investigations;
23 providing assistance in areas of criminal investigations and forensic laboratory services;
24 responding to natural disasters; enforcing hunting laws and boating safety; and many other
25 areas that support the overall mission of crime prevention and public safety for the citizens
26 of Georgia; and
27 WHEREAS, the Georgia Public Safety Memorial Wall was dedicated to honor these brave
28 men and women who made the ultimate sacrifice while protecting life and property in the
29 proud tradition of the public safety services; and
30 WHEREAS, Georgia law enforcement officers put their lives on the line every day as they
31 serve with honor, courage, dignity, and concern for their fellow citizens.
32 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
33 recognize March 10, 2025, as Law Enforcement Appreciation Day at the Capitol and
34 commend law enforcement officers in Georgia for protecting our communities and for
35 putting their lives on the line every day.
36 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
37 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to Georgia law
38 enforcement officers.
